
OVERVIEW
This is an example program of Unix Domain socket programming. Server create a Unix Domain Socket and listening. 
Client connects to server and write int data to socket. And Server accepts the connection and write data from socket and write back to client.

COMPILE
make

FILES
socket.h : Head file of Wrapper.
socket.c : Wrapper of Unix Domain Socket programming interfaces.
server.c : Code of server process.
client.c : Code fo client process.
Makefile  
README  
